@node Legal "Distribution"

@{b}Distribution :@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Even if this program is free, it's not public domain and is copyrighted.

This program may be copied as long as it is accompanied by this doc file both
unaltered  and  no money is charged (except for a reasonable copying fee).

Even if Collector has been tested thoroughly, a nasty hidden bug may be still
present.  All  use  of  this  program  is  at  your  own risk and I assume no
responsibility or liability for any problems that may occur !

All usage of Collector for commercial business is strictly forbidden  without
a written agreement from the author.

@endnode

@node history "History"

@{b}History :@{ub}
~~~~~~~~~

* version 1.00 : First public release.


* version 1.01 : Some minor bugs fixed :

- The slider bar wasn't correctly updated if you deleted more than 5
pictures.

- If you saved an index under an other name than the original one, the new
name wasn't updated...


* version 2.0 : Totally re-written in C, with many improvements.


* version 2.1 :

- Fixed a nasty bug that made Collector crash at runtime  on  some  machines.
Sorry  for  this, and thanks to the people that reported this bug and allowed
me to release this fixed version so fast !

- Now you can append an index at the end of the one currently edited.

- Uses special features of the  MPImage  library  v5.1  in  greyscale  format
(faster, and less memory needed thanks to the library FORCEGREY option). With
this new method and  the  optimisations  done  in  the  new  MPImage  library
version, Collector creates indexes noticeably faster.

- The index completion is now case insensitive.

- Now Collector tells you if it could not find an action associated to a file
type.

- The IndexConv program was totally rewritten.


* version 2.5 :

- Fixed a bug in the recursive addition of thumbnails.

- Now you can choose the way of displaying the  thumbnails  (horizontally  or
vertically).

- You can now run several copies of Collector at the same time.

- When you change thumbnails directories, you now choose the new  directories
via a reqtools requester.

- You can now provide an index name as a CLI argument when running Collector.
You  can also save an icon with an index, so by double-clicking later on this
icon, you can automatically launch Collector and load the index.

- You can now use an autoscrolling screen, by checking the AutoScroll mark in
the screen mode requester.

- Now you can rename / delete / move pictures also on the disk.

- Now the 16 greyscales display should also work on  ECS  machines  (a  68000
version is also provided in the archive).

- New "Complete automatically" function.

- New "Tight display" option

- Some useful informations are now displayed in the screen title bar.

- Improved "Update Index" function.

- You can now choose almost any size for your thumbnails

- You can now make the thumbnails fit totally the frames.

- The text  under  the  thumbnails  can  now  be  displayed  in  bold/italic/
underlined

- Many other internal improvements.


* Version 3.0 :

- You can now export the  indexes  into  IFF  panels.  You  can  also  export
thumbnails into individual IFF files.

- Added the  "Update  Index  Files"  function  for  total  automatic  indexes
updates.

- Added "Quick Scale" option (requires MPImage.library v8.2 or above).

- Added the "Minimize requesters" option.

- Now icons are renamed/moved/deleted along with the pictures files.

- Fixed a bug that caused a software failure when the thumbnails were  taller
than wide.

- Fixed a bug in the sort method.

- Sorting can now be done with different criteria.

- Now the number of added thumbnails is displayed during addition and
completion.

-  Now  the  data  in  the  screen  title   bar   are   updated   while   the
addition/completion.

- Now you can add files with rather "exotic"  names  (containing  parenthesis
and other reserved caracters), without wildcards conflicts.

- Now the "Picture Info" requester pops up if you click on a thumbnail name.

- Added tooltypes handling. For the moment, two tool types  are  available  :
FILE=<index  name>  (loads  this  index  at  each  startup)  and PRIORITY=<n>
(changes Collector priority). (see also @{"Running Collector " link  Running}
for details about launching Collector from CLI ...

- Now if you  move  pictures  with  the  "Change  directory"  function,  file
overwriting is detected...

- If you reach the top/bottom of an multi-volumed index, Collector offers you
to load the previous/next part of this index.

- Now the "Update Index" function checks also for duplicated entries  in  the
index.

- Fixed some minor bugs and made other small improvements...

- Recompiled with SAS 6.58 compiler.


* version 3.2 :

- Added a percentage on the progress bar (hi Paul ! ;-))

- Added the "Save selected only" and "Save selected only as..." functions.

- Now when Collector can't find a file, it says explicitely the name of  this
missing file.

- Now size and resolution is also displayed on IFF panels.

- Fixed a bug in the "Update  index  files"  function,  that  was  preventing
indexes   from   being   updated/sorted   if   these  indexes  were  becoming
multi-volumes.

- Added the "Auto unselect" option.

- Fixed a very nasty bug in the add/complete algorithm (many thanks to  Hervé
Dupont !)

- Rewrote the french doc !

- Improved the file copy routines (they are now much faster).

- Added a progress bar during the "change directory" operation.

- Some minor changes...


* version 3.3 :

- Now Collector checks for windows opened by other programs on its public
screen, before changing its display mode. Without this check, a crash was
generally occuring (thanks to Nils Goers !).

- Now you can have the doc displayed on the screen and still use Collector
normally.

- Added the "Set comment" function.

- Now the thumbnails are unselected by the "AutoUnselect" setting only if
these thumbnails were actually processed.

- Improved the pictures layout in the IFF panels. Now the thumbnails use the
optimal space on the panels, and some names overlaying problems have been
removed.

- Fixed a bug in the IFF panels saving routine, that was generating corrupt
pictures when specifying large dimensions (thanks to Alan Novak !).

- Fixed a bug when using djpeg : djpeg, since it does "on the fly" scaling,
was reporting smaller dimensions than the actual pictures width and height.
So now, when djpeg is used, the jpeg file header is checked directly to get
the right pictures dimensions.
If you have some indexes that contain erroneous data, just load them, select
all the faulty thumbnails, and choose the "Update Info" function. All the
pictures dimensions will be corrected.

- Fixed a bug in the "Update index files" function : when entering a file
pattern in the file selector, the wrong directory was scanned.

- Now the default directory used for the "Change Directory" function is saved
in the preferences file.

- The "Minimize requester" option now discards a few more requesters.

- Added the "All" option to some requesters, to automatize overwriting
existing files.

- Added the "Toggle selection" function.

- Some other minor improvements and bug fixes.


* version 3.5 :

- Added Popup menus ! (can be disabled ;-))

- Now thumbnails/indexes can be exported in various formats (IFF, PNG, JPEG,
PPM and HTML !! (requires pnmtopng for PNG and cjpeg for JPEG).

- Added Top/Bottom/Up/Down buttons for lists items ordering ("Define Actions"
and "Define popup menu" windows).

- Now you can move in the index with the numeric pad.

- Fixed a bug when Collector tried to access data on deleted files.

- When you were checking thumbnails informations, the "changed" flag was
always set to TRUE, so Collector was always asking for a saving confirmation
before loading/quitting. (thanks to Tristan R. Young)

- Now the "AutoUnselect" works properly (and the infos in the title bar are
updated correctly).

@endnode

